'''Nenbutsu-ji''' (念佛寺) is a Buddhist temple of the Jōdo sect located in Nishi Ward, {{ill|Sakai City|ja|堺市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
The temple’s mountain name, Chikuaoyama (乳岡山), is situated at the westernmost end of the {{ill|Hyakusetori Kofun Group|ja|百舌鳥古墳群|1=Mozu Tombs|12=draft}} and is associated with the shrine-temple of {{ill|Ishizutsuta Shrine|ja|石津太神社|12=draft}}, hence once being called "The Temple of the Mountain." In ancient times, a full temple complex (伽藍) existed within the village, and the nearby area of {{ill|Kami Ishizutsu-machi|ja|上石津|12=draft}} was also known as Kannonji-machi.

Historically, the founder’s memorial tablet recorded the inscription "En'yo Yōun Hikyuni, 6th day of June, in the 3rd year of {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft}}" indicating that the temple was indeed rebuilt by Yōun-ni during the {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft}} period. In Showa 55 (1980), due to land development pressures, the temple was relocated to its present site.

== Access ==
* A 10‑minute walk from the {{ill|Nankai Bus|ja|南海バス|12=draft}} stop "Kasumigaoka."
* A 25‑minute walk from {{ill|Ueno-shiba Station|ja|上野芝駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Hankawa Line|ja|阪和線|12=draft}}.

