'''Nenbutsu-ji''' (念佛寺) is a Buddhist temple of the Jōdo sect located in Nishi Ward, {{ill|Sakai|en|Sakai|WD=Q193428|lt=Sakai City|1=Sakai}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|en|Osaka Prefecture|WD=Q122723|lt=Osaka Prefecture|1=Osaka Prefecture}}.

== Overview ==
The temple’s mountain name, Chikuaoyama (乳岡山), is situated at the westernmost end of the {{ill|Mozu Tombs|en|Mozu Tombs|WD=Q4250584|lt=Mozu Tombs|1=Mozu Tombs}} and is associated with the shrine-temple of {{ill|Ishizutsuta Shrine|ja|石津太神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishizutsuta Shrine|1=Iwatsuta Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11586779}}, hence once being called "The Temple of the Mountain." In ancient times, a full temple complex (伽藍) existed within the village, and the nearby area of {{ill|Kami Ishizutsu-machi|ja|上石津|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami Ishizutsu-machi|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} was also known as Kannonji-machi.

Historically, the founder’s memorial tablet recorded the inscription "En'yo Yōun Hikyuni, 6th day of June, in the 3rd year of {{ill|Kyōhō|en|Kyōhō|WD=Q1145048|lt=Kyōhō|1=Kyōhō}}" indicating that the temple was indeed rebuilt by Yōun-ni during the {{ill|Kyōhō|en|Kyōhō|WD=Q1145048|lt=Kyōhō|1=Kyōhō}} period. In Showa 55 (1980), due to land development pressures, the temple was relocated to its present site.

== Access ==
* A 10-minute walk from the {{ill|Nankai Bus|ja|南海バス|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nankai Bus|1=Nankai Bus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11408154}} stop "Kasumigaoka."
* A 25-minute walk from {{ill|Uenoshiba Station|en|Uenoshiba Station|WD=Q856750|lt=Ueno-shiba Station|1=Uenoshiba Station}} on the {{ill|Hanwa Line|en|Hanwa Line|WD=Q1154800|lt=Hankawa Line|1=Hanwa Line}}.

